\cf0 Other complications include that TiVo provides SkipMode only on top 20 channels, only on certain types of shows (not live news or sports), and only on certain shows. Furthermore, SkipMode information is only available arrives later than the show and sometimes not at all. You can change which channels might have SkipMode in Preferences>Channels Finally, SkipMode is not available on TiVo's Suggestions, at least until you save the show for later viewing.\
We've tried to make this as easy as possible to take advantage of SkipMode, while falling back to comskip as needed.  By default, SkipMode is off, as it can interfere with your viewing. Your easiest path to use SkipMode is:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa360\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Enable "Prefer SkipMode to comskip" in Preferences>General.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Enable "Auto SkipMode Active from" and give it a range of time each day you're not going to be watching TV.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Choose Cut or Mark Commercials.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}For each subscription and existing download, enable SkipMode.\
\pard\tx560\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Then for each show that might have SkipMode data (top 20 channels, not news, etc), we will wait up to four hours to finish processing until the SkipMode information is available (or not).  So if you don't need the shows downloaded as soon as possible, then you should be all set. Note there is another difference between Cut and Mark here. As we can Mark a show after it's been downloaded and encoded, we can process the show and then add the chapter-commercial information once it is received. If it is not eventually received, cTiVo will rerun the process with comskip. \
